The paper discusses the Research Software Engineering movement and its importance in supporting the development of software for modern research. This topic is most closely related to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) and Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the need for specialist skill sets and the impact of research software on the wider world, which could be relevant to the Programming Languages (cs.PL), Digital Libraries (cs.DL), and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-categories.
